              <div class="content-area">
                <div class="content-leftside">
                  <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="http://www1.uwindsor.ca">Home</a> / <a href="http://www1.uwindsor.ca/pac">Public Affairs and Communications</a> / <a href="/pac/web-services" class="active">Web Communications</a></div>                                      <h1 class="title">Web Communications</h1>
                                                                                          <div id="node-629" class="node node-type-page"><div class="node-inner">
      <div class="content">
    <p>Web Communications provides support to information providers maintaining Web pages in departments across campus.</p>
<p>Among the services we offer are:</p>
<ul>
<li>
		Regular training courses in writing for University Web sites and creating Web-ready graphics</li>
<li>
		Editorial consultation for perfecting your online message</li>
<li>
		Maintenance of a library of images suitable for use online</li>
<li>
		Design of individual graphics, including animation, to highlight important information</li>
<li>
		Advice and support for site organization and structure</li>
</ul>
<p>The trained graphic designers in Public Affairs&nbsp;help&nbsp;internal clients&nbsp;build a site that is clean, legible and well-organized, yet still exciting,&nbsp;working to develop a distinctive look and create graphics that reflect the objectives of each area.</p>
<p>In addition, the Web communications manager edits <a href="/dailynews"><em>DailyNews</em></a>, the University&rsquo;s e-newsletter distributed to staff, faculty, students, and others interested in the day-to-day workings of campus. To share information with the campus community, be sure to send items of interest to <a href="/dailynews"><em>DailyNews</em></a> at <a href="mailto:uofwnews@uwindsor.ca">uofwnews@uwindsor.ca</a>.</p>
<p>All of the training, consultation and graphic design services of the Web Communications office are offered free of charge to the University community.</p>
<p><strong>Web Communications contact:</strong></p>
<p>	<strong>John Powell</strong><br />
	Director, Web&nbsp;Development<br />
	519-253-3000 ext. 4497<br />
	<a href="mailto:johnpow@uwindsor.ca"><font color="#569bbd">johnpow@uwindsor.ca</font></a></p>
  </div>
  </div></div> <!-- /node-inner, /node -->
